# Advantages of Git

Git provides several benefits:

- Fast and efficient
- Free and open-source
- Works offline
- Reliable data storage
- Complete version history
- Supports branching
- Easy merging
- Excellent collaboration
- Widely used in the software industry

---

# Limitations of Git

Although Git is powerful, it has a few limitations:

- Can be difficult for beginners initially.
- Requires learning command-line commands.
- Merge conflicts can occur when multiple developers edit the same code.

These challenges become easier to manage with practice.

---

# Common Git Terminology

| Term | Meaning |
|------|---------|
| Repository | Storage location for a project |
| Commit | Saved snapshot of the project |
| Branch | Independent line of development |
| Clone | Copy a repository to your computer |
| Push | Upload local commits to a remote repository |
| Pull | Download updates from a remote repository |
| Fetch | Download changes without merging |
| Merge | Combine changes from different branches |

